'''ICASSP''', the '''International Conference on Acoustics, Speech, and Signal Processing''', is an annual flagship conference organized of [[IEEE Signal Processing Society]]. All papers included in its proceedings have been indexed by Ei Compendex.

The first ICASSP was held in 1976 in [[Philadelphia, Pennsylvania]] based on the success of a conference in [[Massachusetts]] four years earlier that had focused specifically on speech signals.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Rabiner|title=The  Acoustics,  Speech,  and  Signal  Processing  Society.  A  Historical  Perspective|date=1984|url=http://www.ece.ucsb.edu/Faculty/Rabiner/ece259/Reprints/216_historical%20perspective.pdf|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref>

As ranked by [[Google Scholar]]'s [[h-index]] metric in 2016, ICASSP has  the highest h-index of any conference in Signal Processing field.

Also, It is considered a high level conference in signal processing and, for example, obtained an 'A1' rating from the Brazilian ministry of education based on its H-index.<ref>[http://www.cs.ecnu.edu.cn/~mlan/SoC-Conference-Ranking.htm SoC Conference Ranking] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110310170217/http://www.cs.ecnu.edu.cn/~mlan/SoC-Conference-Ranking.htm |date=2011-03-10 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.conferenceranks.com/index.html?searchall=ICASSP Conference Ranks]</ref>

