{{Infobox organization |name = International Literacy Association |image = |image_border = |size = <!-- default 200 --> |alt = <!-- alt text; see [[WP:ALT]] --> |caption = |map = <!-- optional --> |msize = <!-- map size, optional, default 200px --> |malt = <!-- map alt text --> |mcaption = <!-- optional --> |abbreviation = |motto = |formation = 1956 <!--{{Start date and years ago|YYYY|MM|DD}}--> |extinction = <!-- date of extinction, optional --> |type = <!-- GO, NGO, IGO, INGO, etc --> |status = <!-- ad hoc, treaty, foundation, etc --> |purpose = [[Literacy]]<!-- focus as e.g. humanitarian, peacekeeping, etc --> |headquarters = {{flagicon|United States}} [[Newark, Delaware]], [[United States]] |location = |coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> |region_served = International |membership = 300,000 |language = <!-- official languages --> |leader_title = President<!-- position title for the leader of the org --> |leader_name = Douglas Fisher <!-- name of leader --> |main_organ = <!-- gral. assembly, board of directors, etc --> |parent_organization = <!-- if one --> |affiliations = <!-- if any --> |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = {{URL|http://www.reading.org/}} |remarks = }} The '''International Literacy Association''' ('''ILA'''), formerly the '''International Reading Association''' ('''IRA'''), is an international [[professional body|professional organization]] that was created in 1956 to improve [[reading (activity)|reading]] instruction, facilitate dialogue about research on reading, and encourage the habit of reading.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.literacyworldwide.org |title=About IRA |publisher=Reading.org |date= |accessdate=2012-08-19}}</ref>
The organization, whose headquarters are in [[Newark, Delaware|Newark]], [[Delaware]], [[United States]], has approximately 300,000 members from 84 countries <ref>https://www.literacyworldwide.org/about-us</ref>, and more than 1,250 councils and affiliates, worldwide.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.reading.org/General/LocalAssociations.aspx |title=Councils and Affiliates |publisher=Reading.org |date= |accessdate=2012-08-19}}</ref> Membership fees range from 24 to 39 dollars, plus fees for journal subscriptions. Discounted subscription rates are available for residents of developing economies.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://marketplace.reading.org/Memberships/IRA_NewMember.aspx |title=Join IRA |publisher=Reading.org |date= |accessdate=2014-03-22}}</ref> The current ILA President is Professor Douglas Fisher. He was as Vice President of the ILA Board of Directors between 2016 and 2017. <ref>https://www.literacyworldwide.org/docs/default-source/biographies/doug-fisher.pdf?sfvrsn=8</ref>
==Publishing== In addition to newsletters, books,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.reading.org/books |title=IRA Books |publisher=Reading.org |date= |accessdate=2012-08-19}}</ref> e-books,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.reading.org/e-books |title=IRA E-books |publisher=Reading.org |date= |accessdate=2012-08-19}}</ref> webinars,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.reading.org/webinars |title=IRA Webinars - Common Core State Standards Webinar Series |publisher=Reading.org |date= |accessdate=2012-08-19}}</ref> and guides, the organization publishes three professional journals: * ''[[The Reading Teacher]]'' &mdash; for those working with children to age 12 * ''[[Journal of Adolescent & Adult Literacy]]'' &mdash; for teachers of older learners * ''[[Reading Research Quarterly]]'' &mdash; publishes contributions in literacy research
''Reading Online'', an [[Electronic journal|e-journal]], sponsored by the organization, was retired in 2005.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.readingonline.org/about/about_index.asp |title=Reading Online |publisher=Reading Online |date= |accessdate=2012-08-19}}</ref> *[http://www.reading.org/reading-today ''Reading Today''], the ILA's membership magazine, was published from 1983 to 2011 as a bi-monthly membership newspaper. From the 2011 August/September issue forward, the publication was split into two parts: a bi-monthly print magazine and an interactive digital e-zine on the Reading Today website.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.reading.org/general/Publications/reading-today |title=Reading Today Online |publisher=Reading.org |date= |accessdate=2014-03-22}}</ref>
== Special Interest Groups == The International Reading Association has over 40 special interest groups for members.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.reading.org/General/AdvocacyandOutreach/SIGS.aspx |title=Special Interest Groups |publisher=Reading.org |date= |accessdate=2012-08-19}}</ref>
==Awards and Grants== ILA offers a number of awards and grants for educators, researchers, and authors.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.reading.org/Resources/AwardsandGrants.aspx |title=IRA Awards and Grants |publisher=Reading.org |date= |accessdate=2012-08-19}}</ref>
==Affiliations== The ILA has been recognized by the United Nations Educational Scientific and Cultural Organization (UNESCO) since 1978; the ILA was reclassified to have Consultative Status with UNESCO in 1996 and continues to hold this status.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ngo-db.unesco.org/r/or/en/1100061872 |title=IRA/UNESCO |publisher=ngo-db.unesco.org |date= |accessdate=2013-03-25}}</ref>
==Annual Conference== The International Literacy Association hosts an annual conference.
